Power Macintosh G4 Memory


I have a fond spot for the Apple PowerMac G4 models as they were the first desktop computers with the ‘velocity engine’ (if I remember correctly). Apparently I bought the much lesser loved ‘yikes’ model, but for what I did this computer served me well and allowed me to work on this here site for years.

Anyway, the ram: you will need either PC 100 or PC 133 168-pin DIMMS for this line with the exception of the later 2002 and 2003 models that accepted PC-2700 SDRAM

Apple PowerMac 5xxx to 9xxx Memory Upgrades


Like some older Macs like the Performa , these are pretty old computers in 2016 and have long been discontinued. But, if you have one either for collecting or even as a daily driver adding more RAM is always a good idea.

These computers take either 30-pin or 72-pin SIMMS depending on specific model.

Apple Performa and Older Memory


These Apple Performa models are pretty dated, with some going back 20 years or more. But, if you still have one that’s in use you can get a bit more life out of by adding some ram.
